	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Bottom line, the NES doesn't have any concept of motion, just static images. A human viewer will perceive motion if a series of images each has small changes in the positions of objects. It's up to your code to make these changes. Since speed is based on how much an object changes position in a given time, you can increase it by having an object make a greater change in position each time it moves.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


