	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe that x_position_lo and x_position_hi are just 16-bit values where x_position_hi acts as a whole value, and x_position_lo acts as a fraction. So it's pretty much just like you'll have x_position_hi as your sprite's X Position. When you have $01 as the x_pos_hi value, and $80 as the x_pos_lo, your sprites X_Pos will be $01. But add $0180 to those values, and you'll get $0300, thus, making your sprites X_Pos $03. Do you understand?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


