		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />you should only add num_0 if the bit you are testing in num_1 is set.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ldx num_1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lda num_0<br /><br />multiply_again:&nbsp; &nbsp;dex<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; beq multiply_end&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; this branch only succeds when X&nbsp; == 0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; adc num_0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; so num_0 will just keep being added to itself<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; jmp multiply_again<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />multiply_end:&nbsp; &nbsp;sta product<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; rts<br /></div><br /></div>
<br />
<br />and also the carry is not being added to the high byte of the product.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
